nded || Right-arm [[Fast bowling|fast]] || [[Delhi cricket team|Delhi]] || [[North Zone cricket team|North]] || align=center| C || ODI, T20I || 96\n|-\n| [[Mohammed Shami]] || {{age|1990|09|03}} || Right-handed || Right-arm [[Fast bowling|fast-medium]] || [[Bengal cricket team|Bengal]] || [[East Zone cricket team|East]] || align=center| A || Test, ODI, T20I || 11\n|-\n| [[Ishant Sharma]] || {{age|1988|09|02}} || Right-handed || Right-arm [[Fast bowling|fast-medium]] || [[Delhi cricket team|Delhi]] || [[North Zone cricket team|North]] || align=center| A || Test || 97\n|-\n| [[Umesh Yadav]] || {{age|1987|10|25}} || Right-handed || Right-arm [[Fast bowling|fast]] || [[Vidarbha cricket team|Vidarbha]] || [[Central Zone cricket team|Central]] || align=center| C || Test, T20I || 19\n|-\n! colspan=\"10\" | Spin bowlers\n|-\n| [[Yuzvendra Chahal]] || {{age|1990|07|23}} || Right-handed || Right-arm [[leg break]] || [[Haryana cricket team|Haryana]] || [[North Zone cricket team|North]] || align=center| B || ODI, T20I || 3\n|-\n| [[Rahul Chahar]] || {{age|1999|08|04}} || Right-handed || Right-arm [[leg break]] || [[Rajasthan cricket team|Rajasthan]] || [[Central Zone cricket team|Central]] || {{n/a}} || T20I || 28\n|-\n| [[Kuldeep Yadav]] || {{age|1994|12|14}} || Left-handed || [[Left-arm unorthodox spin]] || [[Uttar Pradesh cricket team|Uttar Pradesh]] || [[Central Zone cricket team|Central]] || align=center| A || Test, ODI, T20I || 23\n|-\n| [[Shahbaz Nadeem]] || {{age|1989|08|12}} || Right-handed || Slow [[Left-arm orthodox spin|left-arm orthodox]] || [[Jharkhand cricket team|Jharkhand]] || [[East Zone cricket team|East]] || {{n/a}} || Test || 88\n|}\n\nThe BCCI awards central contracts to its players, its pay graded according to the importance of the player. Players' salaries are as follows:\n* Grade A+ \u2013 {{INRConvert|7|c|1}}\n* Grade A \u2013 {{INRConvert|5|c|-3}}\n* Grade B \u2013 {{INRConvert|3|c|-3}}\n* Grade C \u2013 {{INRConvert|1|c|-3}}\n\n;Match fees\nPlayers also receive a match fee of {{INRConvert|15|l}} per Test match, {{INRConvert|6|l}} per ODI, and {{INRConvert|3|l}} per T20I.\n\n==Coaching staff==\n* Head coach: {{flagicon|IND}} [[Ravi Shastri]]\n* Batting coach: {{flagicon|IND}} [[Vikram Rathour]]\n* Bowling coach: {{flagicon|IND}} [[Bharat Arun]] \n* Fielding coach: {{flagicon|IND}} [[Ramakrishnan Sridhar]]\n* Manager: {{flagicon|IND}} Girish Dongre\n* Strength & Conditioning coach: {{flagicon |ENG}} Nick Webb\n* Physiotherapist: {{flagicon |IND}} Nitin Patel\n\n==Tournament history==\n===[[ICC Cricket World Cup]]===\n{{See also|India at the Cricket World Cup}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\" width=85%\n|-\n!colspan=9|World Cup record\n|-\n! width=100 |Year\n! width=150 |Round\n! width=50 |Position\n! width=50 |GP\n! width=50 |W\n! width=50 |L\n! width=50 |T\n! width=50 |NR\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[1975 Cricket World Cup|1975]] ||Round 1||6/8||3||1||2||0||0\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[1979 Cricket World Cup|1979]] ||Round 1||7/8||3||0||3||0||0\n|- style=\"background:gold;\"\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[1983 Cricket World Cup|1983]]||'''Champions'''||1/8||8||6||2||0||0\n|-bgcolor=\"#cc9966\"\n|style=\"border: 3px solid red\"|{{flagicon|IND}}{{flagicon|PAK}} [[1987 Cricket World Cup|1987]]||Semi-finals||4/8||7||5||2||0||0\n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} {{flagicon|NZL}} [[1992 Cricket World Cup|1992]]||Round 1||7/9||8||2||5||0||1\n|-bgcolor=\"#cc9966\"\n|style=\"border: 3px solid red\"|{{flagicon|IND}} {{flagicon|PAK}} {{flagicon|SRI}} [[1996 Cricket World Cup|1996]]||Semi-finals||4/12||7||4||3||0||0\n|-\n|{{flagicon|England}} {{flagicon|IRL}} {{flagicon|NED}} {{flagicon|SCO}} {{Flagicon|Wales}}[[1999 Cricket World Cup|1999]]||R2 (Super 6s)||6/12||8||4||4||0||0\n|- style=\"background:silver;\"\n|{{flagicon|RSA}} {{flagicon|ZIM}} {{flagicon|KEN}} [[2003 Cricket World Cup|2003]]||Runners-up||2/14||11||9||2||0||0\n|-\n|{{flagicon|WIN}} [[2007 Cricket World Cup|2007]]||Round 1||9/16||3||1||2||0||0\n|- style=\"backgr